refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public static staticnullBackedEnum::tryFrom intstringvalue
The tryFrom method translates a string or int into the corresponding Enum case, if any. If there is no matching case defined, it will return null.

&reftitle.parameters;


  value



    The scalar value to map to an enum case.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Basic usage


    The following example illustrates how enum cases are returned.



<?php
enum Suit: string
{
    case Hearts = 'H';
    case Diamonds = 'D';
    case Clubs = 'C';
    case Spades = 'S';
}

$h = Suit::tryFrom('H');

var_dump($h);

$b = Suit::tryFrom('B') ?? Suit::Spades;

var_dump($b);
?>


   &example.outputs;


enum(Suit::Hearts)
enum(Suit::Spades)
